From Michael Heathman Subject Re dogs In article Charles Parr writes What a dog weighs maybe at max You can't handle it You have I presume thumbs Grapple with it and tear it's head off Sheesh even a trained attack dog is no match for a human we have all the Regards Charles Professionals who train guard dogs when polled gave themselves a in chance of survival tackling a trained dog A trained guard dog is not to be trifled An untrained mutt may be another ObMoto A local dog used to chase me all the Really I finally started stopping every time he'd chase He didn't know what to do then and would usually just slink off the After a couple weeks of this he stopped chasing me He would still chase cars or other bikes I think he recognized me when I went by Mike Heathman Briar Rose DoD Lilly Research Titan Awaiting Resurrection Indianapolis IN Where am I to go now that I've gone too far